04/04/2011
ATHENS, Greece -- A passenger airplane made an emergency landing at the international airport in Athens Monday (April 4th) after a bomb threat was received at the office of its operator. The plane, owned by the British tourist company Thomson, was travelling from Great Britain to Egypt. The bomb warning was received at Thomson's office. Two Greek F-16 jets and a Super Puma helicopter escorted the aircraft to the airport in the Greek capital, where it landed. All 213 passengers onboard and the crew are safe. Police are searching the plane. (Ta Nea, To Vima, SKAI, Nafthemporiki - 04/04/11)
